:\"A\",\"addedBy\":\"encasherr@gmail.com\"}},\"candidateResponse\":{\"responseKeys\":[\"A\"]},\"isCorrect\":true},{\"mcqId\":86,\"questionOrderIndex\":35,\"mcq\":{\"id\":86,\"mcq_meta\":{\"choices\":[{\"content\":\"CHAR is fixed length character type at storage level, and that VARCHAR will be variable length.\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"key\":\"A\"},{\"content\":\"CHAR is not a fixed length character type at storage level, and that VARCHAR will be variable length.\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"key\":\"B\"}],\"category\":\"Programming\",\"skill\":\"PLSQL\",\"question\":\"Data Types\",\"description\":\"What is the difference between CHAR and VARCHAR?\",\"minimumExperience\":\"1\",\"maximumExperience\":\"10\",\"score\":\"10\",\"correctAnswer\":\"A\",\"addedBy\":\"encasherr@gmail.com\"}},\"candidateResponse\":{\"responseKeys\":[\"A\"]},\"isCorrect\":true},{\"mcqId\":87,\"questionOrderIndex\":36,\"mcq\":{\"id\":87,\"mcq_meta\":{\"choices\":[{\"content\":\"General functions are of following types:\n1. NVL: Does not convert a null value to an actual value. NVL (exp1, exp2) .If exp1 is null then NVL function return value of exp2.\n2. NVL2: If exp1 is  null, nvl2 returns exp2, if exp1 is null, nvl2 returns exp3. The argument exp1 can have any data type. NVL2 (exp1, exp2, exp3)\n3. NULLIF: Compares two expressions and does not return null if they are equal or the first expression if they are not equal. NULLIF (exp1, exp2)\n4. COALESCE: Returns the first non-null expression in the expression list. COALESCE (exp1, exp2 expn). The advantage of the COALESCE function over NVL function is that the COALESCE function can take multiple alternative values.\n5. Conditional Expressions: Provide the use of IF-THEN-ELSE logic within a SQL statement. Example: CASE Expression and DECODE Function.\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"key\":\"A\"},{\"content\":\"General functions are of following types:\n1. NVL: Converts a null value to an actual value. NVL (exp1, exp2) .If exp1 is null then NVL function return value of exp2.\n2. NVL2: If exp1 is not null, nvl2 returns exp2, if exp1 is null, nvl2 returns exp3. The argument exp1 can have any data type. NVL2 (exp1, exp2, exp3)\n3. NULLIF: Compares two expressions and returns null if they are equal or the first expression if they are not equal. NULLIF (exp1, exp2)\n4. COALESCE: Returns the first non-null expression in the expression list. COALESCE (exp1, exp2 expn). The advantage of the COALESCE function over NVL function is that the COALESCE function can take multiple alternative values.\n5. Conditional Expressions: Provide the use of IF-THEN-ELSE logic within a SQL statement. Example: CASE Expression and DECODE Function.\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"key\":\"B\"}],\"category\":\"Programming\",\"skill\":\"PLSQL\",\"question\":\"Queries\",\"description\":\"Describe different types of General Function used in SQL?\",\"minimumExperience\":\"1\",\"maximumExperience\":\"10\",\"score\":\"10\",\"correctAnswer\":\"B\",\"addedBy\":\"encasherr@gmail.com\"}},\"candidateResponse\":{\"responseKeys\":[\"A\",\"B\"]},\"isCorrect\":true},{\"mcqId\":88,\"questionOrderIndex\":37,\"mcq\":{\"id\":88,\"mcq_meta\":{\"choices\":[{\"content\":\"NVL does not let the programmer substitute a value for a NULL value.\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"key\":\"A\"},{\"content\":\"NVL lets the programmer substitute a value for a NULL value.\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"key\":\"B\"}],\"category\":\"Programming\",\"skill\":\"PLSQL\",\"question\":\"Queries\",\"description\":\"What is the purpose of NVL?\",\"minimumExperience\":\"1\",\"maximumExperience\":\"10\",\"score\":\"10\",\"correctAnswer\":\"B\",\"addedBy\":\"encasherr@gmail.com\"}},\"candidateResponse\":{\"responseKeys\":[\"B\"]},\"isCorrect\":true},{\"mcqId\":89,\"questionOrderIndex\":38,\"mcq\":{\"id\":89,\"mcq_meta\":{\"choices\":[{\"content\":\"SQL is a language not used to communicate with the server to access, manipulate and control data.\nThere are 5 different types of SQL statements.\n1. Data Retrieval: SELECT\n2. Data Manipulation Language (DML): INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, MERGE\n3. Data Definition Language (DDL): CREATE, ALTERR, DROPP, RENAME, TRUNCATE.\n4. Transaction Control Statements: COMMITT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT\n5. Data Control Language (DCL): GRAND, REVOKE\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"key\":\"A\"},{\"content\":\"SQL stands for Structured Query Language. SQL is a language used to communicate with the server to access, manipulate and control data.\nThere are 5 different types of SQL statements.\n1. Data Retrieval: SELECT\n2. Data Manipulation Language (DML): INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, MERGE\n3. Data Definition Language (DDL): CREATE, ALTER, DROP, RENAME, TRUNCATE.\n4. Transaction Control Statements: COMMIT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT\n5. Data Control Language (DCL): GRANT, REVOKE\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"key\":\"B\"}],\"category\":\"Programming\",\"skill\":\"PLSQL\",\"question\":\"Queries\",\"description\":\"What is SQL and also describe types of SQL statements?\",\"minimumExperience\":\"1\",\"maximumExperience\":\"10\",\"score\":\"10\",\"correctAnswer\":\"B\",\"addedBy\":\"encasherr@gmail.com\"}},\"candidateResponse\":{\"responseKeys\":[\"B\"]},\"isCorrect\":true},{\"mcqId\":90,\"questionOrderIndex\":39,\"mcq\":{\"id\":90,\"mcq_meta\":{\"choices\":[{\"content\":\"Group by clause tells oracle to ungroup rows based on distinct values that exists for specified columns. The group by clause creates a data set , containing several sets of records grouped together based on condition.\nHaving Clause: Having clause cannot be used with GROUP BY clause. Having imposes a condition on the group by clause which further filters the group created by the GROUP BY clause.\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"key\":\"A\"},{\"content\":\"Group by clause tells oracle to group rows based on distinct values that exists for specified columns. The group by clause creates a data set , containing several sets of records grouped together based on condition.\nHaving Clause: Having clause can be used with GROUP BY clause. Having imposes 