 the cursor has fetched any row. It is true if rows are fetched\n%NOT FOUN : Checks if the cursor has fetched any row. It is True if rows are not fetched.\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"key\":\"A\"},{\"content\":\"%ISOPEN : Checks if the cursor is open or not\n%ROWCOUNT : The number of rows that are updated, deleted or fetched.\n%FOUND : Checks if the cursor has fetched any row. It is true if rows are fetched\n%NOT FOUND : Checks if the cursor has fetched any row. It is True if rows are not fetched.\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"key\":\"B\"}],\"category\":\"Programming\",\"skill\":\"PLSQL\",\"question\":\"Cursor Attributes\",\"description\":\"Show the cursor attributes of PL/SQL.\",\"minimumExperience\":\"1\",\"maximumExperience\":\"10\",\"score\":\"10\",\"correctAnswer\":\"B\",\"addedBy\":\"encasherr@gmail.com\"}},\"candidateResponse\":{\"responseKeys\":[\"B\"]},\"isCorrect\":true},{\"mcqId\":56,\"questionOrderIndex\":3,\"mcq\":{\"id\":56,\"mcq_meta\":{\"choices\":[{\"content\":\"Intersect is the product of two tables and it lists only matching rows.\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"key\":\"A\"},{\"content\":\"Intersect is not a product of two tables and it lists all rows.\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"key\":\"B\"}],\"category\":\"Programming\",\"skill\":\"PLSQL\",\"question\":\"Intersect\",\"description\":\"What is an Intersect?\",\"minimumExperience\":\"1\",\"maximumExperience\":\"10\",\"score\":\"10\",\"correctAnswer\":\"A\",\"addedBy\":\"encasherr@gmail.com\"}},\"candidateResponse\":{\"responseKeys\":[\"A\"]},\"isCorrect\":true},{\"mcqId\":57,\"questionOrderIndex\":4,\"mcq\":{\"id\":57,\"mcq_meta\":{\"choices\":[{\"content\":\"Cursor is a named private area in SQL from which information can be accessed. They are required to process each row individually for queries which return multiple rows.\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"key\":\"A\"},{\"content\":\"Cursor is a named public area in SQL from which information can be accessed. They are required to process each row individually for queries which return multiple rows.\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"key\":\"B\"}],\"category\":\"Programming\",\"skill\":\"PLSQL\",\"question\":\"Cursor\",\"description\":\"Explain uses of cursor.\",\"minimumExperience\":\"1\",\"maximumExperience\":\"10\",\"score\":\"10\",\"correctAnswer\":\"A\",\"addedBy\":\"encasherr@gmail.com\"}},\"candidateResponse\":{\"responseKeys\":[\"A\"]},\"isCorrect\":true},{\"mcqId\":58,\"questionOrderIndex\":5,\"mcq\":{\"id\":58,\"mcq_meta\":{\"choices\":[{\"content\":\"Procedure allow the DML statements without any restrictions\nFunction does not allow the DML statements \",\"isCorrect\":true,\"key\":\"A\"},{\"content\":\"Procedure does not allow the DML statements without any restrictions\nFunction  allow the DML statements \",\"isCorrect\":false,\"key\":\"B\"}],\"category\":\"Programming\",\"skill\":\"PLSQL\",\"question\":\"Procedure  & Function\",\"description\":\"What is Difference between procedure and function?\",\"minimumExperience\":\"1\",\"maximumExperience\":\"10\",\"score\":\"10\",\"correctAnswer\":\"A\",\"addedBy\":\"encasherr@gmail.com\"}},\"candidateResponse\":{\"responseKeys\":[\"B\"]},\"isCorrect\":false},{\"mcqId\":55,\"questionOrderIndex\":6,\"mcq\":{\"id\":55,\"mcq_meta\":{\"choices\":[{\"content\":\"A syntax error can be easily detected by a PL/SQL compiler. For eg, incorrect spelling.\nA runtime error is handled with the help of exception-handling section in an PL/SQL block. For eg, SELECT INTO statement, which does not return any rows.\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"key\":\"A\"},{\"content\":\"A syntax error cannot be easily detected by a PL/SQL compiler. For eg, incorrect spelling.\nA runtime error is not handled with the help of exception-handling section in an PL/SQL block. For eg, SELECT INTO statement, which does not return any rows.\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"key\":\"B\"}],\"category\":\"Programming\",\"skill\":\"PLSQL\",\"question\":\"Differentiate Errors\",\"description\":\"Differentiate between Syntax and runtime errors.\",\"minimumExperience