ORD.\",\"minimumExperience\":\"1\",\"maximumExperience\":\"10\",\"score\":\"10\",\"correctAnswer\":\"A\",\"addedBy\":\"encasherr@gmail.com\"}},\"candidateResponse\":{\"responseKeys\":[\"A\"]},\"isCorrect\":true},{\"mcqId\":63,\"questionOrderIndex\":7,\"mcq\":{\"questionOrderIndex\":7,\"id\":63,\"mcq_meta\":{\"choices\":[{\"content\":\"A cursor is not implicit by default. The user cannot control or process the information in this cursor.\nIf a query returns multiple rows of data, the program does not defines an explicit cursor. This does not allows the application to process each row sequentially as the cursor returns it.\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"key\":\"A\"},{\"content\":\"A cursor is implicit by default. The user cannot control or process the information in this cursor.\nIf a query returns multiple rows of data, the program defines an explicit cursor. This allows the application to process each row sequentially as the cursor returns it.\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"key\":\"B\"}],\"category\":\"Programming\",\"skill\":\"PLSQL\",\"question\":\"Implicit & Explicit Cursors\",\"description\":\"Define Implicit and Explicit Cursors.\",\"minimumExperience\":\"1\",\"maximumExperience\":\"10\",\"score\":\"10\",\"correctAnswer\":\"B\",\"addedBy\":\"encasherr@gmail.com\"}},\"candidateResponse\":{\"responseKeys\":[\"A\"]},\"isCorrect\":false},{\"mcqId\":64,\"questionOrderIndex\":8,\"mcq\":{\"questionOrderIndex\":8,\"id\":64,\"mcq_meta\":{\"choices\":[{\"content\":\"ROWID is not the logical address of a row, it is  a physical column. It composes of data  number, file  and row number in the data block. Thus, I/O time gets maximized retrieving the row, and results in a faster query.\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"key\":\"A\"},{\"content\":\"ROWID is the logical address of a row, it is not a physical column. It composes of data block number, file number and row number in the data block. Thus, I/O time gets minimized retrieving the row, and results in a faster query.\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"key\":